{
  "texts": [
    "The highest-scored voxel is mapped back to the closest cavity found by either Fpocket or P2Rank and this cavity is taken to be the predicted binding site of the ligand.Model training data preparation: We used an EDock training set having 400 non-redundant proteins [18].",
    "To determine 3D structure similarity across datasets, target structure pairs were formed by selecting one instance from the training set and one instance from each benchmark set.",
    "Subsequently, the TM scores were computed for the aforementioned couples [47].",
    "In the case that the TM-score between a training and validation protein structure exceeded 0.5, the training protein structure was removed from the training set [47].",
    "Hence, it is concluded that there exists no structural relationship between the train and benchmarks.After removing proteins with more than 0.5 TM-Score, the rest of the 290 proteins in the EDock training set were used in molecular docking methods and cavity detector tools."
  ]
}